,"_path":70},"Right vs. Wrong","/lessons/right-vs-wrong",{"title":72,"_path":73},"Knowing Rights","/lessons/knowing-rights",{"title":75,"_path":76},"Natural Law transgressions","/lessons/natural-law-transgressions",{"title":78,"_path":79},"Taxation prohibition licences and permits","/lessons/taxation-prohibition-licences-and-permits",{"title":81,"_path":82},"Force vs. Violence","/lessons/force-vs-violence",{"title":84,"_path":85},"The two pillars of enlightenment","/lessons/the-two-pillars-of-enlightenment",{"title":87,"_path":88},"Ownership","/lessons/ownership",{"title":90,"_path":91},"Conscience","/lessons/conscience",{"title":93,"_path":94},"The law of freedom","/lessons/the-law-of-freedom",{"title":96,"_path":97},"Natural law vs. mans law","/lessons/natural-law-vs-mans-law",{"title":99,"_path":100},"Equality under natural law","/lessons/equality-under-natural-law",{"title":102,"_path":103},"The one true divide","/lessons/the-one-true-divide",{"title":105,"_path":106},"Statism vs. Anarchy","/lessons/statism-vs-anarchy",{"title":108,"_path":109},"The fear of chaos","/lessons/the-fear-of-chaos",{"title":111,"_path":112},"Order Followers","/lessons/order-followers",{"title":114,"_path":115},"Moral culpability","/lessons/moral-culpability",{"title":117,"_path":118},"Responsibility vs. abdication","/lessons/responsibility-vs-abdication",{"title":120,"_path":121},"Self loathing vs. self respect","/lessons/self-loathing-vs-self-respect",{"title":123,"_path":124},"The lost word","/lessons/the-lost-word",{"title":126,"_path":127},"Teaching natural law to others aka the great work","/lessons/teaching-natural-law-to-others-aka-the-great-work",{"title":129,"_path":130},"Shift Happens","/lessons/shift-happens",{"title":132,"_path":133},"The Great Work","/lessons/the-great-work",{"title":135,"_path":136},"At the Crossroads","/lessons/at-the-crossroads",{"title":138,"_path":139},"Conclusion","/lessons/conclusion",{"title":141,"_path":142},"Glossary","/lessons/glossary",{"title":144,"_path":145},"Recommanded Books","/lessons/recommended-books",[147],{"title":148,"_path":149,"children":150},"Challenges","/challenges",[151],{"title":148,"_path":152},"/challenges/main",{"_path":106,"_dir":154,"_draft":155,"_partial":155,"_locale":156,"title":105,"description":157,"cat":158,"id":159,"body":160,"_type":178,"_id":179,"_source":180,"_file":181,"_extension":182},"lessons",false,"","Statism:\nA Statist is a person who erroneously believes that there is such a thing as “authority” vested\nin certain people, giving them the “right” to rule over others. This “authority” means that\ncertain people, who call themselves ‘government,’ have the moral right to issue commands to\nthose whom they rule (those under their jurisdiction), and that their subjects (slaves) have a\n“moral obligation” to obey the arbitrary dictates (laws) set by their “masters.”\nMost simply put, a statist is someone who believes in the legitimacy of slavery.","Lesson","32",{"type":161,"children":162,"toc":175},"root",[163,170],{"type":164,"tag":165,"props":166,"children":167},"element","p",{},[168],{"type":169,"value":157},"text",{"type":164,"tag":165,"props":171,"children":172},{},[173],{"type":169,"value":174},"Anarchy:\nConversely, an Anarchist is a person that knows there could never be legitimacy to\n“authority” or “government” because those terms are simply euphemisms for violence and\nslavery, which are always immoral and in opposition to natural law.\nThe word ‘Anarchy’ is derived from the Greek prefix ‘An- (αν-)’ which means ‘Without / the\nAbsence of’ and the Greek noun ‘Archon (αρχων)’ which means ‘Master / Ruler.’\nAnarchy does not mean ‘Without rules’ – it literally means ‘Without rulers / Without\nmasters.’ The only permanent rules that are in place, are the ones of natural law.\nNo Masters = No Slaves\nIt seems self-evident that anarchy is the true meaning of freedom, and yet, when you ask a\nperson what anarchy means (to them), and what they associate it with, the answer will most\nlikely be: rioting, looting and destroying other people’s property, in one word; chaos.\nWhich is literally the exact opposite of what anarchy truly is.",{"title":156,"searchDepth":176,"depth":176,"links":177},2,[],"markdown","content:1.lessons:32.statism-vs-anarchy.md","content","1.lessons/32.statism-vs-anarchy.md","md"]